1
00:00:12,467 --> 00:00:14,700
<i> Best birthday ever!</i>

2
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:16,233
<i>Daddy and Mommy made a huge
effort</i>

3
00:00:16,367 --> 00:00:17,667
<i> to surprise me, didn't they?</i>

4
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:19,000
<i>Is that really the only reason?</i>

5
00:00:19,133 --> 00:00:21,967
<i>You looked so happy when
you and Gerald were dancing.</i>

6
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:23,433
<i> I think I like him.</i>

7
00:00:23,567 --> 00:00:26,467
<i>If I ever have a boyfriend,
I want one like Gerald.</i>

8
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:28,833
<i>Well, what if I told you
that I like you too?</i>

9
00:00:28,967 --> 00:00:30,500
<i> Not all the people</i>

10
00:00:30,633 --> 00:00:32,600
<i>who you consider friends
are your friends.</i>

11
00:00:32,733 --> 00:00:34,133
<i> I don't want you getting hurt,</i>

12
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:36,933
<i>and I hate that
you're fooled by anyone.</i>

13
00:00:37,067 --> 00:00:38,433
<i> You made me look like a fool!</i>

14
00:00:38,567 --> 00:00:40,433
<i>Wow! Is that the one
who looks like a fool?</i>

15
00:00:40,567 --> 00:00:41,700
<i> Your birthday was so grand,</i>

16
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:43,033
<i>everyone thinks
you're so beautiful</i>

17
00:00:43,167 --> 00:00:44,767
<i> and your parents even came!</i>

18
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:46,867
<i>So you have no right
to complain!</i>

19
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,467
<i> Half of my wings are gone.</i>

20
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:50,833
<i>But I know that
I will still be okay.</i>

21
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:53,533
<i>Because this is not
the life for me.</i>

22
00:00:53,667 --> 00:00:56,533
<i>I belong in the US,
with my parents.</i>

23
00:00:56,667 --> 00:00:58,233
<i> Goodbye, Betsy.</i>

24
00:00:58,367 --> 00:00:59,567
<i> I thought you were on leave</i>

25
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:03,267
<i>for your anniversary celebration
with Mark.</i>

26
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:04,633
<i> He had a work thing, Dad.</i>

27
00:01:04,767 --> 00:01:06,033
<i> He had to fly to Hong Kong.</i>

28
00:01:06,167 --> 00:01:08,967
<i>You know how demanding
his work is, right?</i>

29
00:01:18,333 --> 00:01:20,233
<i> Oh my God!</i>

30
00:01:20,367 --> 00:01:22,067
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no.

31
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:24,733
Gina, Gina! Let me explain!

32
00:01:24,867 --> 00:01:27,467
What are you going to explain
to me, Mark?

33
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:28,800
What? Are you going to tell me

34
00:01:28,933 --> 00:01:31,300
everything you
and that girl doing

35
00:01:31,433 --> 00:01:34,267
while you're here,
cheating on me?

36
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:40,233
All I did was think of ways to
show you how much I love you!

37
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,367
Oh my god, Mark!

38
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:43,500
How could you do this?

39
00:01:43,633 --> 00:01:45,800
Is there anything missing?

40
00:01:45,933 --> 00:01:47,933
I try my best to
understand you, right?

41
00:01:48,067 --> 00:01:51,367
I did my best to be a
good girlfriend to you!

42
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:53,567
I gave it my all, Mark!

43
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:56,267
I spent five years of
my life loving you!

44
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:59,767
I risked everything just
to make this relationship work!

45
00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:00,700
How about you?

46
00:02:00,833 --> 00:02:02,500
How about you?
Did you love me, Mark?

47
00:02:02,633 --> 00:02:04,433
Tell me the truth!

48
00:02:04,567 --> 00:02:05,900
Sorry, sorry.

49
00:02:06,033 --> 00:02:07,967
Sorry? You're so thick-faced!

50
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:09,100
- Sorry, I messed up.
- You lied.

51
00:02:09,233 --> 00:02:10,100
You're lying!

52
00:02:10,233 --> 00:02:11,433
It's too much!

53
00:02:11,567 --> 00:02:13,167
I'm suffocating.

54
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:15,267
But believe me, I loved you!

55
00:02:15,433 --> 00:02:16,400
Suffocated?

56
00:02:16,533 --> 00:02:17,800
Do you feel suffocated?

57
00:02:17,933 --> 00:02:19,100
You're lying!

58
00:02:19,233 --> 00:02:21,900
If you're not happy anymore,
you should have just said so!

59
00:02:22,033 --> 00:02:23,733
I'll understand!

60
00:02:23,867 --> 00:02:24,733
But you're a coward!

61
00:02:24,867 --> 00:02:26,367
You led me on!

62
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,533
Do you think I didn't
see all the signs?

63
00:02:28,667 --> 00:02:30,333
That you didn't intend to
take me seriously,

64
00:02:30,467 --> 00:02:32,767
I saw them all
but I turned a blind eye,

65
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:34,800
because I love you so much!

66
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:39,367
But I just wasted
my life for you!

67
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:43,200
You know truth be told, Gina,
good riddance.

68
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:45,867
That man has no bones!

69
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,367
Why? What happened?

70
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,233
I caught him with another woman.

71
00:03:52,033 --> 00:03:53,333
Oh my goodness.

72
00:03:53,467 --> 00:03:54,233
Where is that man?

73
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,633
I'll talk to him.

74
00:03:55,767 --> 00:03:56,600
Call him, call him.

75
00:03:56,733 --> 00:03:57,833
- I'll talk to him.
- Dad, stop! Okay?

76
00:03:57,967 --> 00:04:01,233
If I could have it my way,
I wouldn't have told you,

77
00:04:01,367 --> 00:04:04,267
because you've told me several
times that you don't like Mark.

78
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:06,633
I'm just stubborn.

79
00:04:06,767 --> 00:04:07,500
And look what happened?

80
00:04:07,633 --> 00:04:09,000
You're right.

81
00:04:09,133 --> 00:04:11,800
He took me for granted,
he even fooled me.

82
00:04:11,933 --> 00:04:15,767
You don't cry over that
kind of man

83
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:18,000
and you have to be strong!

84
00:04:18,133 --> 00:04:23,267
But Mom, I built
my life around him.

85
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:27,133
We were together for five years,
and he just dumped me like that?

86
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:32,600
At least now you can think
about your goals, your life.

87
00:04:32,733 --> 00:04:35,433
Gina, you have so much life
ahead of you.

88
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:39,067
I don't want to love anymore,
I don't want to get hurt.

89
00:04:40,333 --> 00:04:41,300
It's my fault too,

90
00:04:41,433 --> 00:04:42,967
because I'm the one who's making
a fool of myself.

91
00:04:45,233 --> 00:04:47,133
Gina, this is what you'll do.

92
00:04:47,267 --> 00:04:51,233
Don't think about it anymore,
don't take it to heart.

93
00:04:51,367 --> 00:04:55,533
You just made the mistake
of loving the wrong person.

94
00:04:55,667 --> 00:04:57,767
One of these days,
one of these days,

95
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,433
just wait for it.

96
00:04:59,567 --> 00:05:03,933
You'll find a man
who truly loves you.

97
00:05:04,100 --> 00:05:06,333
Dad, you know the truth is,

98
00:05:06,467 --> 00:05:08,467
I don't know if that day
will ever come.

99
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,100
It will come, it will come.

100
00:05:10,233 --> 00:05:14,533
I can't just follow
my heart, Dad.

101
00:05:14,667 --> 00:05:17,333
I'd rather commit to someone
that truly loves me,

102
00:05:17,467 --> 00:05:18,867
and not just someone
saying he loves me

103
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,733
but in the end
he'll just leave me too.

104
00:05:22,333 --> 00:05:23,500
Check.

105
00:05:23,633 --> 00:05:24,100
That's right.

106
00:05:26,233 --> 00:05:28,233
Baby.

107
00:05:31,233 --> 00:05:34,000
No, I need all hands here
for the anniversary sale.

108
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:36,000
So you have to be here
on Saturday, okay?

109
00:05:36,133 --> 00:05:37,200
And that's final.

110
00:05:39,567 --> 00:05:42,733
Ma'am, I really
need this day off.

111
00:05:42,867 --> 00:05:45,833
Amy, you already know
the schedule, right?

112
00:05:45,967 --> 00:05:48,200
It's just that our wedding
rehearsal was moved

113
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:49,967
to this Saturday.

114
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:52,533
Our parents are flying
in from out of state.

115
00:05:52,667 --> 00:05:54,167
Wedding rehearsal?

116
00:05:54,300 --> 00:05:56,100
Excuse me, Amy.

117
00:05:56,233 --> 00:05:58,967
You have wedding rehearsals
on Saturday, right?

118
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:00,833
- Yes.
- Okay, good.

119
00:06:00,967 --> 00:06:02,533
Take the day off, no, no.

120
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:03,833
Take two days off.

121
00:06:03,967 --> 00:06:06,833
I want you to make sure that you
get that wedding right, okay?

122
00:06:06,967 --> 00:06:07,867
Thank you, Sir Robert.

123
00:06:08,033 --> 00:06:09,433
You're welcome.

124
00:06:09,567 --> 00:06:10,067
Okay.

125
00:06:14,567 --> 00:06:16,933
I know it's hard what
you are going through.

126
00:06:17,067 --> 00:06:20,867
But I want you to know
that I am here for you.

127
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,467
I'm okay, Dad.

128
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:24,633
I'm just a little stressed
at our anniversary sale.

129
00:06:24,767 --> 00:06:27,433
But, I'm fine.

130
00:06:27,567 --> 00:06:28,433
Okay.

131
00:06:28,567 --> 00:06:30,800
You have to acknowledge
that it's hard.

132
00:06:30,933 --> 00:06:32,000
I'd be lying, Dad,

133
00:06:32,133 --> 00:06:36,633
if I said that I know that
Mark and I won't last long.

134
00:06:36,767 --> 00:06:39,233
But I was willing to
work on it with him.

135
00:06:39,367 --> 00:06:42,300
Let's look at this as a
blessing in disguise.

136
00:06:42,467 --> 00:06:44,567
Because if that happened
later on,

137
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:46,000
it might have hurt more.

138
00:06:46,133 --> 00:06:49,800
Now, what we need to learn now,
right now!

139
00:06:49,933 --> 00:06:52,867
How do we bounce back, okay?

140
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,633
You can do that.

141
00:06:54,767 --> 00:06:56,433
Come here.

142
00:06:56,567 --> 00:06:57,333
Give me a hug.

143
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,933
Okay, why don't you do this?

144
00:07:02,067 --> 00:07:05,333
Why don't you just go home
to the Philippines?

145
00:07:05,467 --> 00:07:06,667
- Well...
- But I wouldn't know

146
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:07,767
what to do there.

147
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:10,400
I don't know what I plan
to do with my life.

148
00:07:10,533 --> 00:07:12,633
Me, I know.

149
00:07:12,767 --> 00:07:14,433
Come here, call your friends.

150
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,533
Go to Boracay,
whatever you want to do.

151
00:07:16,667 --> 00:07:19,933
You know, you need a break
from this breakup.

152
00:07:20,067 --> 00:07:21,367
You need to enjoy!

153
00:07:24,133 --> 00:07:27,667
<i>We just landed at Filipinas
International Airport.</i>

154
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,467
<i> Welcome to Manila!</i>

155
00:07:36,667 --> 00:07:37,767
Excuse me, Mister.

156
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:39,233
Will that still take long?

157
00:07:39,367 --> 00:07:42,800
Ma'am, the new battery
is on its way.

158
00:07:42,933 --> 00:07:44,033
I'm sorry.

159
00:07:44,167 --> 00:07:45,167
Okay.

160
00:07:55,133 --> 00:07:58,400
Auntie Connie, I'm going to be
a little late getting home.

161
00:07:58,533 --> 00:08:02,333
Our car broke down,
but they said it'll be fixed.

162
00:08:04,433 --> 00:08:05,733
Okay.

163
00:08:05,867 --> 00:08:06,533
Okay.

164
00:08:08,667 --> 00:08:09,367
Yes.

165
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:14,000
This is a hold-up!

166
00:08:14,133 --> 00:08:15,400
Shut up.

167
00:08:15,533 --> 00:08:17,200
Okay, I won't fight.

168
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,333
Help!

169
00:08:22,467 --> 00:08:24,033
Let go of me!

170
00:08:24,167 --> 00:08:25,067
Hey!

171
00:08:29,567 --> 00:08:30,833
Oh my God.

172
00:08:37,167 --> 00:08:38,200
Miss, are you okay?

173
00:08:38,333 --> 00:08:40,900
- I'm okay.
- Are you hurt?

174
00:08:41,033 --> 00:08:41,833
You're so meddlesome!

175
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:45,200
Oh my God!

176
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:48,267
Hey!

177
00:08:50,367 --> 00:08:52,433
- What's that?
- Mister, help us!

178
00:08:52,567 --> 00:08:53,567
Hey!

179
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:54,333
- Hey!
- Chase him, Mister!

180
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,867
- He's escaping now!
- Hey!

181
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,767
Hey!

182
00:08:57,900 --> 00:08:58,567
Call for help.

183
00:08:58,700 --> 00:09:01,133
Mister, please. Call a medic!

184
00:09:01,267 --> 00:09:02,833
Help!

185
00:09:02,967 --> 00:09:05,533
- Help!
- Are you okay?

186
00:09:05,667 --> 00:09:06,600
Gina?

187
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:09,767
Gerald?

188
00:09:15,900 --> 00:09:17,600
You're a registered
nurse now.

189
00:09:17,733 --> 00:09:19,567
Where do you work?

190
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:21,433
No, I quit.

191
00:09:21,567 --> 00:09:22,967
The salary is so low.

192
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,700
I'm working at a BPO now.

193
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:27,867
My office is near
where you were robbed.

194
00:09:28,033 --> 00:09:30,767
Well, I need to make
a lot of money.

195
00:09:30,900 --> 00:09:32,333
I'm supporting Betsy.

196
00:09:32,467 --> 00:09:35,800
She just took the licensure exam
to become a registered nurse.

197
00:09:35,933 --> 00:09:38,567
Oh, so you and Betsy
are still together.

198
00:09:40,967 --> 00:09:42,833
Okay, I'll just get something.

199
00:09:42,967 --> 00:09:43,900
Okay.

200
00:09:50,933 --> 00:09:52,633
Gerald!

201
00:09:52,767 --> 00:09:54,833
What happened to you?

202
00:09:54,967 --> 00:09:57,133
Why did you go there?

203
00:09:57,267 --> 00:09:58,833
- What happened to you?
- Ouch. Ouch.

204
00:09:58,967 --> 00:10:00,367
Sorry!

205
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:01,333
What are you doing?

206
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:03,400
Why did you pass there?

207
00:10:03,533 --> 00:10:04,567
It's more economical that way.

208
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:06,033
Just one ride, right?

209
00:10:06,167 --> 00:10:07,533
That's why I rode there.

210
00:10:07,667 --> 00:10:10,167
It's cheaper but you
almost got killed.

211
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:11,600
Gerald...

212
00:10:11,733 --> 00:10:13,533
Killed when I'm alive!

213
00:10:13,667 --> 00:10:15,200
This is nothing.

214
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:16,700
This is far from vital organs,

215
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:20,267
anyway, the stab
was just superficial.

216
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:21,633
Are you sure?

217
00:10:21,767 --> 00:10:23,400
Are you okay?

218
00:10:23,533 --> 00:10:24,333
Are you okay?

219
00:10:24,467 --> 00:10:26,067
It's a little painful,
but it's okay.

220
00:10:29,133 --> 00:10:30,767
- My poor baby.
- It's okay.

221
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:31,667
Love you, love you!

222
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:33,167
Oh, love you, love you,
love you.

223
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:34,800
Hey, I'm ticklish.

224
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:36,567
Well, don't do that anymore.

225
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:39,600
Okay, okay.

226
00:10:39,733 --> 00:10:40,767
Well, it's...

227
00:10:45,367 --> 00:10:46,167
Gina?

228
00:10:53,033 --> 00:10:54,000
Hi, Betsy.

229
00:10:58,767 --> 00:11:01,500
It looks like you guys
are still talking.

230
00:11:01,633 --> 00:11:02,867
I'll just leave.

231
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,167
Wait, Gina! Wait a minute!

232
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:09,200
When did you get home?

233
00:11:09,367 --> 00:11:10,033
Just a while ago.

234
00:11:12,633 --> 00:11:17,100
Hey, thanks for bringing
Gerald to the hospital.

235
00:11:17,233 --> 00:11:22,400
But, you're also the reason
why my boyfriend got wounded.

236
00:11:24,967 --> 00:11:27,433
I'm sorry about that, Betsy.

237
00:11:27,567 --> 00:11:28,133
Hey, what are you?

238
00:11:28,267 --> 00:11:29,500
Just kidding!

239
00:11:29,633 --> 00:11:31,867
We're okay, aren't we?

240
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,933
Hey, you didn't get in touch.

241
00:11:34,067 --> 00:11:35,900
I thought you were dead.

242
00:11:36,033 --> 00:11:37,300
Joke!

243
00:11:37,433 --> 00:11:39,467
Hey, how are you?

244
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:42,067
You know, I heard something.

245
00:11:42,233 --> 00:11:44,900
I can't remember
who told me that.

246
00:11:45,033 --> 00:11:47,567
About two, or three years ago.

247
00:11:47,700 --> 00:11:51,067
They said you came home
with your boyfriend.

248
00:11:54,533 --> 00:11:56,067
Betsy, I really have to go.

249
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:58,333
Wait!

250
00:11:58,467 --> 00:12:00,167
Let me guess.

251
00:12:00,300 --> 00:12:02,167
You were fooled, right?

252
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:03,833
Come on, Betsy.

253
00:12:03,967 --> 00:12:06,367
Come on too, Gina!

254
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:08,133
What's with you?

255
00:12:08,267 --> 00:12:13,633
Somehow we've been through
something, I know you well.

256
00:12:13,767 --> 00:12:15,100
So he fooled you, right?

257
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:18,667
Let me see his picture!

258
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:21,267
Tell him, he's not allowed
to come to our area

259
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:23,300
or else I'll stab him.

260
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:27,333
Come on, let me see.

261
00:12:27,467 --> 00:12:31,567
You know that's impossible
because he's in the US.

262
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:34,367
Anyway, I'm so happy

263
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:36,633
that you and Gerald are still
going strong.

264
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:40,333
Thanks.

265
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:42,733
Imagine, we'd last that long?

266
00:13:05,567 --> 00:13:10,333
Hey, Gina,
are you still mad at me?

267
00:13:10,467 --> 00:13:11,800
Oh, what? No!

268
00:13:13,833 --> 00:13:17,067
You know we were so young then,

269
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:19,933
and I still remember we fell
into the pool

270
00:13:20,067 --> 00:13:21,967
because we were both
being dramatic.

271
00:13:22,133 --> 00:13:24,533
I mean, it's so stupid.

272
00:13:24,667 --> 00:13:26,400
Yeah, it's so embarrassing.

273
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:32,033
Hey, but okay if you don't have
a bad feeling about me anymore,

274
00:13:32,167 --> 00:13:32,933
let's catch up!

275
00:13:33,067 --> 00:13:34,133
I'll give you my number.

276
00:13:36,233 --> 00:13:37,900
Okay.

277
00:13:38,033 --> 00:13:39,000
Oh, here, here. There you go.

278
00:13:43,367 --> 00:13:44,600
09...

279
00:13:48,133 --> 00:13:49,067
There.

280
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,267
Text me.

281
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:51,467
I don't have any load.

282
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:05,267
It was really nice
seeing you again, Betsy.

283
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:06,533
Me too.

284
00:14:06,667 --> 00:14:07,633
I'll go ahead.

285
00:14:07,767 --> 00:14:09,433
Gerald, I'll go ahead.

286
00:14:09,567 --> 00:14:10,467
Oh, thank you.

287
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:11,900
- Be careful, be careful.
- Thank you.

288
00:14:12,033 --> 00:14:12,767
Bye.

289
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:17,800
Gerald

290
00:14:17,933 --> 00:14:19,067
What?

291
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,967
I heard what you
were saying, Love.

292
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:23,400
Oh, that's English, catch up.

293
00:14:23,533 --> 00:14:24,467
Gerlad, what now?

294
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:26,033
When will you get better?

295
00:14:26,167 --> 00:14:27,200
This will be quick.

296
00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:28,267
It's your fault!

297
00:14:31,933 --> 00:14:33,167
Gina!

298
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:35,700
If you had asked me
to pick you up,

299
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,800
maybe you'll not be robbed.

300
00:14:37,933 --> 00:14:40,800
And you have not encountered
that couple!

301
00:14:40,933 --> 00:14:42,267
Auntie, it was meant to happen.

302
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:44,767
I think about how long
I've been avoiding them,

303
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:47,633
and then they're the first
people here that I encounter.

304
00:14:51,667 --> 00:14:55,367
Well, why do you seem so happy?

305
00:14:55,500 --> 00:15:01,967
Auntie, if I were to be honest,
I was glad to see Betsy again.

306
00:15:02,133 --> 00:15:07,000
Nothing has changed about her,
she's still just as perky.

307
00:15:07,133 --> 00:15:08,733
I miss her too.

308
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,467
Let me help you.

309
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:33,433
- No. I'll do it.
- I'll do it.

310
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:39,300
Betsy.

311
00:15:39,433 --> 00:15:41,900
Did you and Gina talk
after you meet at the hospital?

312
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:44,567
No.

313
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:46,367
She texted,
but I said I was busy.

314
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:51,933
I thought you wanted
to catch up with her.

315
00:15:52,067 --> 00:15:55,733
I just said that so I could say
something in English.

316
00:15:55,867 --> 00:15:58,967
We're not BFFs
like we used to be.

317
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:02,033
Besides, she still seems
to be upset with me.

318
00:16:03,267 --> 00:16:05,800
Betsy, that's a long time ago.

319
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:08,433
I just wanted to ask her
which hospital we can work

320
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:09,667
in the US.

321
00:16:19,533 --> 00:16:21,667
Oh, here's your tea.

322
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:24,700
Why are you stalking your ex?

323
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:28,367
Gina, you won't get
anything out of that.

324
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:30,900
You know, why don't you
go out of the house!

325
00:16:31,033 --> 00:16:33,533
Go bond with your friends!

326
00:16:33,667 --> 00:16:35,367
Auntie, even if I have
friends before,

327
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:37,533
I only go out with Betsy.

328
00:16:40,767 --> 00:16:43,600
You know, I know you weren't
okay when you went to America.

329
00:16:43,767 --> 00:16:45,600
Why is that?

330
00:16:45,733 --> 00:16:48,333
We don't need Gina!

331
00:16:48,467 --> 00:16:51,567
Besides, she won't help us
because she's still bitter!

332
00:16:57,400 --> 00:17:03,367
You know let's just wait for the
results of my board exams.

333
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:06,033
The reason is very petty,
Auntie.

334
00:17:06,167 --> 00:17:08,600
Actually, that's why
I wanted to reach out to Betsy

335
00:17:08,733 --> 00:17:13,167
because I was the reason why
our communication was cut off.

336
00:17:13,300 --> 00:17:18,033
I want to at least
make up with her.

337
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,533
Auntie, thank you for the tea.

338
00:17:21,767 --> 00:17:23,100
I'll just go up.

339
00:17:23,233 --> 00:17:24,233
Okay.

340
00:17:30,133 --> 00:17:31,800
Betsy...

341
00:17:31,933 --> 00:17:34,033
We are close in achieving our
dreams.

342
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:43,233
Thank you because you're
the one sacrificing for us.

343
00:17:43,367 --> 00:17:48,033
You can go ahead of me
since you're a registered nurse.

344
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,800
But you still want us
to be together.

345
00:17:52,167 --> 00:17:53,200
That's why I love you.

346
00:17:56,667 --> 00:17:58,600
I love you more.

347
00:17:58,733 --> 00:18:00,967
I will do everything
for our dream, okay?

348
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:07,700
You should because you'll
never find a woman like me.

349
00:18:17,733 --> 00:18:21,367
When we're finally in America,

350
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:25,333
everything Gina has
I can have it too.

351
00:18:28,533 --> 00:18:32,900
I'm no longer the poor friend
she left behind.

352
00:18:33,033 --> 00:18:38,067
I'll prove that
I can match Gina.

353
00:19:11,300 --> 00:19:13,067
You're drunk.

354
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:14,033
You drank a lot.

355
00:19:14,167 --> 00:19:18,767
What are you going to do,
without me?

356
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:20,867
You're something else.

357
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,467
- Watch your head.
- Mother!

358
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:23,933
Did you take my money here?

359
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:28,700
Yes, because it's
Hubby's birthday,

360
00:19:28,867 --> 00:19:31,267
I treated our friends.

361
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:34,333
See? He's so drunk and wasted.

362
00:19:34,467 --> 00:19:37,233
I don't care about
your boyfriend!

363
00:19:37,367 --> 00:19:40,333
Why did you use my money?

364
00:19:40,467 --> 00:19:41,600
That's my money,
that's my allowance!

365
00:19:41,733 --> 00:19:44,933
Gerald gave that to me!

366
00:19:45,067 --> 00:19:47,200
Well, just ask again!

367
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:50,433
You're acting as if it's like
he gave you millions of money!

368
00:19:50,567 --> 00:19:52,600
You're something else.

369
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:55,100
Do you still expect you'll
get rich there?

370
00:19:55,233 --> 00:19:56,833
You won't get rich
with that man!

371
00:19:56,967 --> 00:19:59,600
You won't be successful.

372
00:19:59,733 --> 00:20:01,167
Do you think Gerald and I
will last long

373
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:03,133
if that's what I think?

374
00:20:03,300 --> 00:20:05,700
You're wrong, Mother.

375
00:20:05,833 --> 00:20:08,033
Gerald will take me
out of poverty

376
00:20:08,167 --> 00:20:10,767
and I'll get something from him!

377
00:20:10,900 --> 00:20:13,733
Unlike you who get easily
gets fooled by some guy!

378
00:20:13,867 --> 00:20:14,933
Hey!

379
00:20:15,067 --> 00:20:16,200
You talk too much!

380
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:19,900
You haven't proven anything yet!

381
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:26,500
Don't worry, when Gerald
and I go to America,

382
00:20:26,633 --> 00:20:28,333
who are you to me!

383
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:34,700
You'll die here, old, fat,

384
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:38,400
eaten by worms because all your
boyfriends don't care about you!

385
00:20:38,567 --> 00:20:39,900
Damn you, Betsy!

386
00:20:40,033 --> 00:20:41,200
Ever since you've
just a problem!

387
00:20:41,333 --> 00:20:42,633
That's enough!

388
00:20:54,733 --> 00:20:56,933
Oh my!

389
00:20:57,067 --> 00:20:59,500
My life is toxic, Gina!

390
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:05,000
You know this is still the
place I go,

391
00:21:05,133 --> 00:21:06,733
whenever I'm in a bad mood.

392
00:21:11,433 --> 00:21:12,900
<i> See you at the park, okay?</i>

393
00:21:13,033 --> 00:21:13,633
<i> Bye!</i>

394
00:21:19,967 --> 00:21:21,900
<i> Let me go!</i>

395
00:21:22,033 --> 00:21:24,167
<i>- Shut up!
- Let me go!</i>

396
00:21:24,300 --> 00:21:25,600
<i> Help!</i>

397
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,900
<i> Betsy!</i>

398
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:43,233
Hey, sorry.

399
00:21:45,967 --> 00:21:46,800
Are you still scared

400
00:21:46,933 --> 00:21:49,267
because of what happened to us
before?

401
00:22:14,567 --> 00:22:16,500
Actually...

402
00:22:16,667 --> 00:22:19,800
it's a good thing
that you brought me here.

403
00:22:19,933 --> 00:22:20,933
What happened was traumatic,

404
00:22:21,067 --> 00:22:25,533
but what doesn't kill you makes
you stronger, right?

405
00:22:27,233 --> 00:22:30,733
In fairness,
you've changed a lot.

406
00:22:30,867 --> 00:22:34,200
You're no longer the Gina
who used to cry and whine

407
00:22:34,333 --> 00:22:35,533
that I knew.

408
00:22:46,767 --> 00:22:48,433
But you know, Betsy,

409
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:52,900
I'll never forget what you did
for me.

410
00:22:53,033 --> 00:22:57,267
I'm really grateful
for what you did.

411
00:22:57,400 --> 00:23:00,833
Hey, I'll charge you for that!

412
00:23:00,967 --> 00:23:03,533
What if...

413
00:23:03,667 --> 00:23:06,833
What if you just
take me to America?

414
00:23:06,967 --> 00:23:08,000
As in now!

415
00:23:11,067 --> 00:23:16,100
I just want to leave
my miserable life here.

416
00:23:16,233 --> 00:23:23,400
Even the most difficult thing
in my life, my mother.

417
00:23:26,133 --> 00:23:29,033
Betsy, she's still your mother.

418
00:23:29,167 --> 00:23:33,400
You can only say that
because your mother is fine.

419
00:23:33,533 --> 00:23:39,300
I just want to fly even
if my wings are all broken.

420
00:23:39,433 --> 00:23:40,300
It's hard, Gina.

421
00:23:42,233 --> 00:23:43,233
It's so hard.

422
00:23:45,233 --> 00:23:52,300
You know, every day
poverty hits us.

423
00:23:52,433 --> 00:23:59,267
I want to experience
life like yours.

424
00:24:04,467 --> 00:24:09,333
Betsy, you also have things...

425
00:24:09,467 --> 00:24:11,967
that I also want for myself.

426
00:24:12,100 --> 00:24:15,167
But that's life.

427
00:24:15,300 --> 00:24:18,567
You don't get
everything you want.

428
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:20,267
Yes, it's true.

429
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:22,267
Your drama is still the same.

430
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:24,267
You're rich but abandoned.

431
00:24:26,067 --> 00:24:27,800
While me, I'm still poor.

432
00:24:29,300 --> 00:24:31,033
But promise!

433
00:24:31,167 --> 00:24:33,400
I won't let myself
get stuck here.

434
00:24:36,467 --> 00:24:39,900
When I pass the nursing
licensure exam,

435
00:24:40,033 --> 00:24:41,600
everything will go as planned.

436
00:24:41,733 --> 00:24:44,067
Gerald and I can go to America.

437
00:24:46,767 --> 00:24:51,433
By the way, the NLE results
will be out next week.

438
00:24:51,567 --> 00:24:53,433
Gerald will prepare a
celebration for me,

439
00:24:53,567 --> 00:24:54,733
you're invited.

440
00:25:01,967 --> 00:25:04,267
Gerald is making all the
sacrifices for both of you.

441
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:05,767
And you're dating someone else?

442
00:25:05,900 --> 00:25:08,267
I'm flirting with that AFAM.

443
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:10,933
He's going to be my ticket
and Gerald's to America!

444
00:25:11,067 --> 00:25:12,567
That guy has a criminal record!

445
00:25:12,700 --> 00:25:14,667
I want you right now,
right here.

446
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:15,400
No!

447
00:25:15,533 --> 00:25:16,367
What's with you?

448
00:25:16,500 --> 00:25:18,967
Is my desperation
reaching a new level?

449
00:25:19,100 --> 00:25:20,700
I really want to help you.

450
00:25:20,833 --> 00:25:25,033
You know what Gerald and I need,
to get out of here.
